Description: Limestone relief of Tjetji: this slab bears a finely carved, low relief figure of the lady Tjetji who is shown wearing a long, tightly fitting dress and a heavy wig. There is no colour.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: B. Porter & R. Moss, 'Topographical Bibliography of Ancient Egyptian Hieroglyphic Texts, Reliefs and Paintings' IV (Oxford: Clarendon Press), III, p. 67.
Bibliographic references: James 1961 / Hieroglyphic texts from Egyptian stelae, etc. Part 1 (pl.4)
